# CLAUDE.md

## SESSION START - CHECK FOR IN-PROGRESS WORK

At the start of every session, before responding to the user, check for in-progress work:

1. Check if `.planning/WIP.md` exists — if yes, read it and present the resumption context to the user
2. If no WIP.md, check if `.planning/STATE.md` exists and has any segments marked `IN_PROGRESS` or `BLOCKED`
3. If in-progress work is found, briefly present the status and ask: "Resume from where we left off, or start something new?"
4. If no in-progress work is found, proceed normally

This check is lightweight (2 file reads) and ensures work is never silently lost between sessions.

