## GTI Workflow

### Commands (invoke via `/gti:command`)

| Command | When |
|---------|------|
| `/gti:progress` | Check status, route to next action |
| `/gti:plan-phase N` | Create detailed plan for phase |
| `/gti:execute` | Run current approved plan |
| `/gti:pause-work` | Create handoff for later |
| `/gti:resume-work` | Continue from handoff |
| `/gti:add-issue` | Log deferred issue |

### Subagents

| Agent | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| gti-researcher | Gather context before planning |
| gti-planner | Create PLAN.md |
| gti-executor | Execute plan segments, fix bugs |
| gti-reviewer | Verify completion, run tests |

### Mandatory GTI Sequence

> Every implementation task MUST follow this sequence. No exceptions.

```
researcher -> planner -> (user approval) -> commit plan -> executor -> reviewer
```

After user approval and before spawning the first executor, the orchestrator MUST commit PLAN.md and any planning artifacts. Executors write per-segment `SUMMARY-XX.Y.md` files to the phase directory and commit them with their code.

### State Files

```
.planning/
├── PROJECT.md    # What we're building
├── ROADMAP.md    # Phase breakdown
├── STATE.md      # Current position (READ THIS FIRST)
├── ISSUES.md     # Deferred work
├── WIP.md        # Work-in-progress (auto-updated during execution)
└── phases/XX-name/
    ├── PLAN.md          # Phase plan (committed before execution)
    ├── SUMMARY-XX.Y.md  # Per-segment summaries (written by executor)
    └── SUMMARY.md       # Phase summary (written by reviewer)
```

